e on button click assign textbox box to hidden field','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','publish',NULL,NULL,'Y','279,124,240'),(9675,'jQuery mark Checkbox Checked on button click','jquery-checkbox-checked-button-click','<!-- wp:shortcode -->\r\n[ads]\r\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>jQuery set checkbox as checked:</strong> Here in this article we will learn how in jQuery we can mark our checkboxes as checked whenever user click on specific button. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"jQuery (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://codepedia.info/category/jquery-tutorials/\" target=\"_blank\">jQuery</a> is a fast, small, and features rich JavaScript library. It makes things like HTML document traversal and manipulation easy.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>So today we will see if we have a checkbox in our HTML page (form element). And wants to marked that checkbox as checked depend upon some value or condition. Then by using<strong> .prop()</strong> method we able to achieve the same.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:quote -->\r\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><strong>.Prop() </strong>: The prop() method sets or returns properties and values of the selected elements.</p></blockquote>\r\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><br>Let\'s see the code, how it will work.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3># Html Code: Add button and a checkbox.</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Here we added a checkbox and give it id as myCheckbox, along with a input button tag having id as myButton. <br>Now on <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"button click (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://codepedia.info/click-event-for-dynamic-button-jquery/\" target=\"_blank\">button click</a> we make the checkbox as checked.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:code {\"className\":\"language-markup\"} -->\r\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code language-markup\"><code>\r\n&lt;input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"myCheckBox\"/&gt; My Checkbox\r\n&lt;input type=\"button\" id=\"myButton\" value=\"Click Me\" /&gt; \r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<!-- /wp:code -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator -->\r\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\">\r\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3># jQuery Code: Use .prop() method to make checkbox checked</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:code {\"className\":\"language-js\"} -->\r\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code language-js\"><code>\r\n$(\"#myButton\").on(\'click\',functino(){\r\n  $(\"#myCheckBox\").prop(\"checked\", true); \r\n});\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<!-- /wp:code -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Here in above code on button click, we have use<strong> .prop()</strong> method and set attribute <strong>checked as true,</strong> which marked as<strong> checked</strong>.  If we set attribute <strong>checked as false</strong> then this will <strong>unchecked </strong>the checkbox. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>You can also check how to unchecked the checkbox in jquery with live example.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> Here in this article we able to change our checkbox values. That is by using .prop() method we set our checkbox checked as well as unchecked. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong># Other Resource:</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><li><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"http://api.jquery.com/prop/\" target=\"_blank\">.prop() method</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/checkbox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Checkbox (opens in a new tab)\">Checkbox</a></li></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Hope you enjoyed this tutorial. If you have any recommendations, please let us know what you think in the comment section below! See you again next time! </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','article/jquery-checkbox-get-set-values_637410523057813021.jpg',NULL,'1',124,NULL,'How to mark checkbox as checked in jQuery',NULL,'Using .prop() how we can mark checkbox as checked in jQuery. With jQuery .prop() method we can set or get properties of selected element.','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','2020-11-16 21:05:36.079703','publish',NULL,NULL,'Y','297,124,2'),(9694,'How to add table row in jQuery','add-table-row-jquery','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>[ads] <strong>Add table row in jQuery:</strong> Here in this article we learn 4 different ways to add table row in jQuery on button click. i.e how to append row to  table tbody.  Methods like <code>.append()</code>, <code>prepend()</code>, <code>.after()</code> and <code>.before()</code>  are used to add table rows. </p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Lets see each of these method with an example. Before that we just add a button and table and 2 texboxes for our example. Here html code looks like as show below</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>HTML CODE :</strong> <br><br></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:code -->\r\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>Name &lt;input id=\"txtName\" type=\"text\" /&gt; Location &lt;input id=\"txtLocation\" type=\"text\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;button id=\"btnAddRow\"&gt;Add New Row &lt;/button&gt;\r\n&lt;br/&gt;\r\n&lt;br/&gt;\r\n&lt;table border=\"1\" id=\"myTable\"&gt;\r\n  &lt;thead&gt;\r\n    &lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;\r\n    &lt;th&gt;Location&lt;/th&gt;\r\n  &lt;/thead&gt;\r\n  &lt;tr id=\"trow\"&gt;\r\n    &lt;td&gt;Satinder singh&lt;/td&gt;\r\n    &lt;td&gt;Mumbai&lt;/td&gt;\r\n  &lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<!-- /wp:code -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2># Using .append()</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>By using <strong>.append()</strong> method we add element at the end of the table i.e at the last index.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',NULL,NULL,'1',124,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-05-13 20:15:40.267629','0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','2020-07-17 20:18:27.000000','publish',NULL,NULL,'Y','124'),(9695,'Test Image 1212','test-image-upload','<h3>hello welcome to the datda asasasas 1212 ediyteddd</h3><p>&nbsp;</p><pre><code class=\"lang-js\"> \r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 12.25px;\"><code class=\"html\"> $(\"document\").ready(function(){\r\n         // logic here.\r\n  var a=\"hello world\";\r\n  alert(\"a\");\r\n}); </code> </pre></code></pre><p><br></p><hr><p><br></p><pre><code class=\"lang-cs\"> Public void Main(){\r\n  string a=\"Hello world\";\r\n  Console.WriteLine(a);\r\n} </code></pre><p><br></p><hr><p><br></p><pre><code class=\"lang-html\">&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;One &lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;One &lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;One &lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt; \r\n </code></pre><p><br></p>','g2_637261388340864548.jpg',NULL,'1',161,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-05-29 12:10:56.372491','0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','2020-06-26 01:15:45.000000','draft',NULL,NULL,'Y','161,278,47'),(9696,'asd','asd','<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;;\">ï»¿sdsd</span><br></p>',NULL,NULL,'1',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','2020-05-15 09:23:58.862758','0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','draft',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL),(9697,'er','er','<p>wersd asd asd&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,'1',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','2020-05-26 18:48:24.787299','draft',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL),(9698,'JavaScript convert negative number to positive','javascript-convert-negative-number-to-positive','<div><b>Converting negative to positive: </b>Here in this article we will learn how in JavaScript&nbsp;we can convert any negative number to positive number. This can be done in two different ways.&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div>For example we can use simple mathematics logic or we can use build-in function. But we also want to know which method is faster in converting negative number to positive.&nbsp;</div><h2>2 ways to convert negative number to positive.</h2><ol><li>Using simple mathematics logic</li><li>Using pre-build function Math.Abs()</li></ol><div><br></div><div>Let\'s get in details of each method one by one.</div><h2><span style=\"font-size: 1.53125rem; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Method 1: Using mathematics logic.</span></h2><div>Here first we have to make sure that the value should be negative, for that we can check with if condition that&nbsp; number value should be less then 0 (ZERO).&nbsp;So we can multiply it with -1, as by multiplying it gives us a&nbsp;<b>positive value</b>.</div><div><br></div><div>Let see how our JavaScript code look&nbsp;</div><pre><code class=\"lang-js\"> \r\n// function which convert negative value to positive.\r\nfunction ConvertToPositive(foo){\r\n	var bar=0;\r\n	// check our value should be in negative\r\n	if(foo&lt;0)\r\n	{\r\n		bar=foo*-1; // multiply by -1\r\n	}\r\n	// return positive value;\r\n	return bar; \r\n}\r\n </code></pre><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">Now we call this JavaScript function , which gives alert message with the positive value. See the below code</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><br></span></div><pre><code class=\"lang-js\"> // declare variable and assign negative value to it.\r\n   var foo=-10;\r\n<br>   alert(ConvertToPositive(foo)); </code></pre><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><br></span></div><div>Its simply gives alert message which call our js function \'ConvertToPositive\' and return a positive value.&nbsp;</div><div>Wow!! we are done with method 1.</div><h2>Method 2: Using Math.Abs() function.</h2><div>JavaScript function <b>Math.Abs()</b> return the absolute value of the given number. If the given value is not a number, then it return NAN. And if given number is null, then it return 0.</div><div><br></div><div>Now look at our below JavaScript code, to see the usage of <b>math.abs() </b>pre-build function.</div><pre><code class=\"lang-js\"> var foo = Math.abs(-13);\r\n<br> var bar = Math.abs(null); </code></pre><div><br></div><div>Here foo return positive value as 13, and bar result zero as it have null value.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Conclusion:</b> Here we learn 2 different method for converting negative number to positive number in JavaScript. In method 1 we use simple mathematics logic, and in method 2 we use JavaScript pre-build Math.abs() function.</div><div><br></div><div>Both method gives us desired output. But as per benchmark method 1 i.e using mathematic logic is faster then math.abs() pre-buld function.</div> ',NULL,NULL,'1',297,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-05-29 09:42:56.298174','0001-01-01 00:00:00.000000','2020-05-29 09:42:56.298174','publish',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL),(9705,'This is angular tutorial','this-is-angular-tutorial','<p>this is amy new artilce on angular js&nbsp;</p><p>asasas s</p><pre><code class=\"lang-js\"> hasas\r\nasas</code> </pre><p><br></p>',NULL,NULL,'1',278,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','2020-09-09 00:00:00.000000','publish',NULL,NULL,'Y','190,24,52,278'),(9706,'post title','a_pst_slug','a_pst_content longtext','a_pst_featured_img ',NULL,'a_pst_author_id ',1,NULL,'a_pst_meta_title ','a_pst_meta_keyword ','a_pst_meta_description','2020-05-30 00:25:02.000000','2020-05